OL,3,C'This drought is killing us': Sicilian
OL,4,Clocals left without running water
OL,6,FProfessor Paola Quattrini at Sicily's
OL,7,Fprincipal university sees little sign
OL,8,Fof things improving.
OL,10,F"Dry seasons are longer, and when it
OL,11,Frains it rains in a very severe and
OL,12,Fviolent way, so the soils are not able
OL,13,Fto absorb water, so there is run off
OL,14,Fand soil erosion," she said.
OL,16,FA similar process, known as
OL,17,Fdesertification, is seen often in
OL,18,FNorth Africa, of once fertile areas
OL,19,Fbeing turned to arid wasteland.
