OL,3,C'This drought is killing us': Sicilian
OL,4,Clocals left without running water
OL,6,FBut at the problem grips southern
OL,7,FEurope, farmers are forced to face the
OL,8,Frealities of unreliable and
OL,9,Funsustained rainfall.
OL,11,FFarmer Francesco Capizzi described the
OL,12,Fsituation as being "very close" to
OL,13,Fdesert-like.
OL,15,F"We feel the smell of the desert. For
OL,16,Fsome years the weather has been slowly
OL,17,Fpushing us towards this new era," he
OL,18,Fadded.
